above).  This is on by default.
.TP 8
.B \-C
If set,
.B bash
does not overwrite an existing file with the
.BR > ,
.BR >& ,
and
.B <>
redirection operators.  This may be overridden when
creating output files by using the redirection operator
.B >|
instead of
.BR > .
