.I arg
is to be read and executed when the shell receives
signal(s)
.IR sigspec .
If
.I arg
is absent (and there is a single \fIsigspec\fP) or
.BR \- ,
each specified signal is
reset to its original disposition (the value it had
upon entrance to the shell).
