.B \-P
option forces a
.SM
.B PATH
search for each \fIname\fP, even if
.if t \f(CWtype -t name\fP
.if n ``type -t name''
would not return
.IR file .
If a command is hashed,
.B \-p
and
.B \-P
print the hashed value, which is not necessarily the file that appears
first in
.SM
.BR PATH .
